01:26:23.881 --> 01:26:27.460
You get instantaneous production
from the Jeeve-meister.

01:26:27.486 --> 01:26:29.218
Drone's a much tougher nut.

01:26:29.220 --> 01:26:32.789
- It is so beautiful out here.
- Yeah.

01:26:32.791 --> 01:26:35.491
You should see it in the spring
when the wind blows.

01:26:35.493 --> 01:26:38.828
You can see ripples.
It's like water.

01:26:38.830 --> 01:26:42.032
- It's like the ocean, but real green.
- Mmm.

01:26:42.034 --> 01:26:43.767
It really is.

01:26:45.737 --> 01:26:48.371
It's kind of calm. Real pretty.

01:26:50.374 --> 01:26:53.309
You hungry? Uh, yeah. Kind of.

01:26:53.311 --> 01:26:57.313
But, um... God, I don't
think I want to go back.

01:26:58.148 --> 01:27:00.430
Yeah, I know how you feel.

01:27:04.186 --> 01:27:06.955
Should probably get going though.
Okay.

01:27:06.957 --> 01:27:10.188
Hey, let me take you
someplace nice this time.

01:27:10.214 --> 01:27:11.450
It'll be on Jann.

01:27:14.564 --> 01:27:16.397
Thanks for holding the bag, man.
Of course.

01:27:16.399 --> 01:27:18.760
I gotta eat something. I'm,
like, suddenly starving. Mmm.

01:27:23.972 --> 01:27:26.473
You don't like pickles.
Oh, come on.

01:27:26.475 --> 01:27:28.208
What? What, the whole
world needs to know...

01:27:28.210 --> 01:27:30.277
what my mother's known for
years... I'm a picky eater?

01:27:30.279 --> 01:27:32.012
Okay, I'm putting it away.
Thank you.

01:27:32.014 --> 01:27:33.513
All right.

01:27:33.515 --> 01:27:35.014
Can I give 'em a fry?

01:27:35.016 --> 01:27:36.316
No. Come on.

01:27:36.318 --> 01:27:38.117
All right, go for it.
Hey, Jeeve-meister.

01:27:38.119 --> 01:27:39.718
Hey!

01:27:40.686 --> 01:27:41.953
Watch this. What?

01:27:41.955 --> 01:27:44.956
Jeeves. Jeeves. Sit.

01:27:44.958 --> 01:27:48.160
Jeeves, sit. Sit.

01:27:48.162 --> 01:27:49.761
Sit. Perfect.

01:27:49.763 --> 01:27:53.532
Sit. God. Drone gets super
obedient when food is around.

01:27:53.534 --> 01:27:55.800
Jeeves is still
kind of a wild man.

01:27:55.802 --> 01:27:58.769
Do not leave food out around him.
He will go for it.

01:27:59.538 --> 01:28:01.539
Good boy.

01:28:01.541 --> 01:28:03.073
You're such a good...

01:28:03.075 --> 01:28:05.676
You're not gonna make me look like
I'm one of those insane old women...

01:28:05.678 --> 01:28:07.778
who talks to their dogs, are you?
Um, no.

01:28:07.780 --> 01:28:09.179
Don't worry about it.

01:28:09.181 --> 01:28:11.549
I am worried about it. My
dogs are gonna be offended.

01:28:11.551 --> 01:28:14.218
The dogs are not gonna
read this article.

01:28:14.220 --> 01:28:16.420
I gotta tell you. Hmm?

01:28:16.422 --> 01:28:19.223
They've never taken to a man
the way they've taken to you.

01:28:19.225 --> 01:28:20.624
Really? Nah.

01:28:20.626 --> 01:28:22.392
Except me, of course.
Yeah. Yeah.

01:28:22.394 --> 01:28:24.795
Oh. Can you hold this?

01:28:24.797 --> 01:28:26.730
Yeah, of course.

01:28:32.903 --> 01:28:34.470
Hello?

01:28:35.238 --> 01:28:37.573
Hey.

01:28:38.441 --> 01:28:40.442
Yes, I would like to, um...

01:28:40.444 --> 01:28:42.445
I can't right now.
I got this guy here.

01:28:42.447 --> 01:28:44.180
<i>What guy?</i>

01:28:47.016 --> 01:28:49.151
<i>Rolling Stone</i> guy, yeah.

01:28:50.052 --> 01:28:52.412
You know, can I just
meet you there?

01:28:53.321 --> 01:28:56.424
Okay. Great. Yeah, perfect.

01:28:56.426 --> 01:28:58.426
I'll see you then. Bye.

01:29:02.230 --> 01:29:03.830
All right. Well, I should...

01:29:03.832 --> 01:29:06.600
I should probably get out of here,
let you get on with your life.

01:29:06.602 --> 01:29:11.303
That's, no... It's... There's just
this dance that I like to go to.

01:29:12.139 --> 01:29:13.939
Sorry. You dance?

01:29:13.941 --> 01:29:15.607
Yeah.

01:29:15.609 --> 01:29:18.010
It's something I've discovered over
the past couple years I really like.

01:29:18.012 --> 01:29:19.478
Although I'm not that good
at it yet.

01:29:19.480 --> 01:29:21.413
Wait, sorry.
What kind of dancing?

01:29:22.348 --> 01:29:24.950
I tend to do, like,
the jerk, the swim.

01:29:24.952 --> 01:29:27.652
You know, like,
cheesy '70s disco.

01:29:27.654 --> 01:29:30.722
Really? Yeah. It's one of the
things about living in Bloomington.

01:29:30.724 --> 01:29:33.257
It's like a time warp. You're
completely hip if you do that.

01:29:33.259 --> 01:29:36.427
Yeah, right. So, where do you go?
To a club?

01:29:37.395 --> 01:29:39.435
I go to this Baptist church.

01:29:40.030 --> 01:29:41.564
Why... Why do you go there?

01:29:42.098 --> 01:29:43.798
Baptists can dance.

01:29:43.800 --> 01:29:46.967
Wow. Dancing.

01:29:46.969 --> 01:29:48.736
I will not vogue.

01:29:48.738 --> 01:29:52.005
<i>That is where I put my foot
down. I do not vogue.</i>

01:29:52.007 --> 01:29:55.075
<i>Yeah. It's really cool though.
Like a lot of people show up.</i>

01:29:55.077 --> 01:29:57.343
<i>And they got their
dancin' shoes on.</i>

01:29:57.345 --> 01:30:01.614
<i>It's good. It's nice. Everyone for the
most part just leaves each other alone.</i>

01:30:06.319 --> 01:30:08.987
<i>I thought it might be nice
before you go, if...</i>

01:30:08.989 --> 01:30:13.125
uh, maybe we could exchange
address data or something?

01:30:13.127 --> 01:30:14.759
Yeah. Absolutely.

01:30:14.761 --> 01:30:18.096
<i>Yeah. I'll get my stuff together.
Great.</i>

01:30:18.098 --> 01:30:20.598
<i>I'll start carving an ice
sculpture out of my car.</i>

01:30:20.624 --> 01:30:22.191
<i>It's like Antarctica out there.</i>

01:30:44.892 --> 01:30:49.096
Uh, dog stuff. Throw toys. Chew toys.
Crap stains on carpet.

01:30:49.098 --> 01:30:54.001
Uh, fireplace. American flag.
Shark doll on bookcase.

01:30:54.003 --> 01:30:56.236
Alanis poster. Uh, soda cans.

01:30:56.238 --> 01:30:58.638
Lots of them. There's Pepsi.
There's Mountain Dew.

01:30:58.640 --> 01:31:02.509
Um, looks like a frat.
A kind of bookish frat.

01:31:02.511 --> 01:31:05.211
Uh, there's a Botticelli
calendar... <i>Birth of Venus.</i>

01:31:05.213 --> 01:31:09.315
Uh, wooden chess set.
Postcard of Updike.

01:31:09.317 --> 01:31:14.286
Um, brain comparison...
male, female, dog. Cartoon.

01:31:15.688 --> 01:31:18.123
In the bedroom, there is a
Barney towel used as a curtain.

01:31:18.125 --> 01:31:20.892
There is a tennis ball. There's
a dental floss on top of books.

01:31:20.894 --> 01:31:24.096
There's a photo collage of his family,
the kind kids put in their dorm rooms.

01:31:24.098 --> 01:31:28.033
His sister is kind of pretty. She
looks like a female version of him.

01:31:28.035 --> 01:31:30.879
There is, uh, stuff everywhere.
Clothes everywhere.

01:31:30.905 --> 01:31:32.137
Sneakers on the floor.

01:31:32.139 --> 01:31:33.938
Clothes draped over stuff.

01:31:35.775 --> 01:31:37.442
Uh...

01:31:37.444 --> 01:31:40.711
Blue toilet-seat cover,
looks like a rug.

01:31:40.713 --> 01:31:44.115
Postcards.
Clintons, um, baboons.

01:31:44.117 --> 01:31:46.817
A Saint Ignatius quote.

01:31:46.819 --> 01:31:49.821
"Lord, teach me to be generous. Teach
me to serve you as you deserve."

01:31:49.823 --> 01:31:53.659
To give and not to count the cost.
To toil and not to seek for rest.

01:31:53.661 --> 01:31:56.628
To labor and not to ask
for reward...

01:31:56.630 --> 01:31:59.998
"save that of knowing
that I do your will."

01:33:27.395 --> 01:33:29.095
Hey.

01:33:29.097 --> 01:33:31.998
Tell you what. Riding around
in that rental of yours.

01:33:32.000 --> 01:33:35.134
That feeling of gliding? This thing
doesn't even have shock absorbers.

01:33:35.136 --> 01:33:36.669
What... What is it?

01:33:36.671 --> 01:33:38.270
It's just an old Civic.

01:33:38.272 --> 01:33:41.374
I know it doesn't look like much.
But, man, this thing starts.

01:33:41.376 --> 01:33:44.043
It's actually a problem.
Why is that a problem?

01:33:44.045 --> 01:33:46.925
I gotta get a new one, but I
can't junk this. Why not?

01:33:47.980 --> 01:33:49.213
It's my friend.

01:33:49.215 --> 01:33:50.981
Ah.

01:33:53.585 --> 01:33:55.152
Hey, David. I, uh...

01:33:56.354 --> 01:33:58.188
Wow. Just happened
to have one on you, huh?

01:33:58.190 --> 01:34:02.392
Yeah. I mean, I... I did debate
whether or not I should do this.

01:34:02.394 --> 01:34:04.026
Why? I don't know.

01:34:04.028 --> 01:34:07.797
Don't you think it's some kind of
kid-brother sort of thing to do?

01:34:07.799 --> 01:34:11.033
No. Thank you. I look
forward to reading this.

01:34:11.035 --> 01:34:15.304
Oh, you're welcome. I put my
address and e-mail on the flyleaf.

01:34:15.306 --> 01:34:18.341
Oh. Okay. Cool.

01:34:18.343 --> 01:34:22.611
I'll, uh... Yeah, I'll read it after I finish
the Heinlein, and I'll send you a note.

01:34:22.613 --> 01:34:25.615
That's great. Thanks.

01:34:25.617 --> 01:34:28.483
Be interesting to be inside
your head for a while.

01:34:30.420 --> 01:34:33.288
I like your cover.
Yeah. Yeah, me too.

01:34:33.290 --> 01:34:36.625
I actually had them use the same
art for the British edition.

01:34:36.627 --> 01:34:39.427
Come on. You got
approval, and I d...

01:34:44.066 --> 01:34:45.466
It's nice. It's very nice.

01:34:45.468 --> 01:34:49.070
Don't worry about it. It was not
such a... not such a big success.

01:35:07.992 --> 01:35:10.860
Hey, isn't it at all reassuring to
have a lot of people read you...

01:35:10.862 --> 01:35:13.903
and, you know, say that you're
a really strong writer?

01:35:15.932 --> 01:35:18.634
It'll be interesting to
talk to you in a few years.

01:35:18.636 --> 01:35:20.469
Why do you say that?

01:35:21.637 --> 01:35:24.573
My experience is that
that is not so.

01:35:26.909 --> 01:35:29.043
The more people think
you're really great,

01:35:29.045 --> 01:35:31.813
actually the bigger the fear
of being a fraud is, you know?

01:35:31.815 --> 01:35:34.949
The worst thing about getting a
lot of attention paid to you...

01:35:34.951 --> 01:35:36.918
is that you're afraid
of bad attention.

01:35:36.920 --> 01:35:39.453
And if bad attention hurts you,

01:35:39.455 --> 01:35:43.290
the caliber of the weapon
pointing at you has gone way up.

01:35:43.292 --> 01:35:46.660
Like from a .22 to a .45. Mmm.

01:35:46.662 --> 01:35:50.430
Look, there are parts of me that want a lot
of attention and think I'm really great...

01:35:50.432 --> 01:35:52.965
and want other people
to see it.

01:35:55.002 --> 01:35:58.704
I think that's one of the ways you
and I are sort of alike, you know?

01:36:00.140 --> 01:36:03.775
All right. Hey, uh... All right.

01:36:09.682 --> 01:36:11.784
Fuck. David.

01:36:15.988 --> 01:36:18.270
I'm not so sure
you want to be me.

01:36:19.224 --> 01:36:20.691
I don't.

01:36:21.659 --> 01:36:24.094
Give my best to Jann.

01:38:24.533 --> 01:38:26.734
<i>"When I think of this trip,".</i>

01:38:26.736 --> 01:38:30.871
<i>I see David and me
in the front seat of his car.</i>

01:38:30.873 --> 01:38:33.673
<i>We are both so young.</i>

01:38:33.675 --> 01:38:35.909
<i>He wants something better
than he has.</i>

01:38:35.911 --> 01:38:39.479
<i>I want precisely
what he has already.</i>

01:38:39.481 --> 01:38:43.116
Neither of us knows where
our lives are going to go.

01:38:44.451 --> 01:38:46.819
It smells like chewing tobacco,

01:38:46.821 --> 01:38:50.390
soda and smoke.

01:38:50.392 --> 01:38:54.461
And the conversation is
the best one I ever had.

01:38:59.634 --> 01:39:04.737
<i>David thought books existed
to stop you from feeling lonely.</i>

01:39:04.739 --> 01:39:08.208
<i>If I could, I'd say to David that
living those days with him...</i>

01:39:08.210 --> 01:39:10.076
<i>reminded me
of what life is like,</i>

01:39:10.078 --> 01:39:13.980
instead of being
a relief from it.

01:39:15.415 --> 01:39:19.018
"And I'd tell him it made
me feel much less alone."

01:40:51.191 --> 01:40:52.859
I need to use your bathroom
for a second.

01:40:52.861 --> 01:40:55.461
I believe it's unoccupied.

01:41:09.174 --> 01:41:11.543
It's me talkin'
into the tape recorder.

01:41:14.947 --> 01:41:18.750
And Drone's sittin' behind me
just chillin' out.

01:41:18.752 --> 01:41:22.587
I'm smoking. Having just said I
wouldn't smoke, I'm smoking.

01:41:25.625 --> 01:41:28.059
Just me and your tape recorder.

